# Example environment variables for Netlify (do NOT commit real secrets)
TWITCH_CLIENT_ID=your_twitch_client_id_here
TWITCH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_twitch_client_secret_here
# Optional (legacy):
# TWITCH_OAUTH=Bearer your_oauth_token_here

# Optional Redis URL for caching, token storage and rate-limiting (recommended for production)
# REDIS_URL=redis://:password@hostname:6379/0

# For deployment & monitoring automation (Option A):
# Create a Netlify Personal Access Token and add it to your repo secrets as `NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN`.
# Also add your Netlify Site ID as `NETLIFY_SITE_ID`.
# Add `ALERT_WEBHOOK` to receive alerts (optional); otherwise alerts create GitHub issues.


